race.description: Ray White Pakenham & Officer Maiden Plate
race.comment: ZEACTION (4) should take a power of beating. Three runs this time in have netted three minor placings, stepping up to this sort of trip at Yarra Valley and running a good race for second behind an impressive winner. He'll be better for that and should take plenty of beating. GRINZINGER TUNDRA (5) was much better last time out at Cranbourne when boxing on for a narrow defeat. He's another who has found his sort of trip and can break through. LUCKY CHANCE (3) was beaten as an odds-on favourite second up at Warrnambool but is worth another chance with added fitness. HAYAI TSURU (9) is third up and an each-way hope.
